@startuml subjects-schema
!theme plain
title Figure 3.4. Subjects Collection – Schema Detail

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
hide circle

skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  BorderColor #1565C0
  HeaderBackgroundColor #1565C0
  HeaderFontColor white
}

class "subjects" <<MongoDB Collection>> {
  .. Primary Key ..
  **_id** : ObjectId <<auto-generated>>
  .. Required Fields ..
  **name** : String [required, maxlength: 150]
  **category** : String [required]
  **owner** : ObjectId → users [required, ref: "User"]
  .. Optional Fields ..
  thumbnail : String [default: ""]
  description : String [maxlength: 5000, default: ""]
  featured : Boolean [default: false]
  .. Status ..
  status : String [enum: "Draft" | "Published" | "Unpublished" | "Inactive", default: "Draft"]
  .. Audit Fields ..
  createdBy : ObjectId → users [ref: "User"]
  updatedBy : ObjectId → users [ref: "User"]
  .. Timestamps ..
  createdAt : Date [auto]
  updatedAt : Date [auto]
}

note right of "subjects"
  **Indexes:**
  - name: text index (full-text search)
  - status: regular index
  - category: regular index
  - owner: regular index
  - featured: regular index
  - createdAt: descending index

  **Status Lifecycle:**
  Draft → Published → Unpublished
                    → Inactive (soft delete)

  **Business Rules:**
  - BR-SUB-005: Only Admin can create
  - BR-SUB-007: Expert can update assigned only
  - BR-SUB-008: Only Admin can publish/unpublish
  - BR-SUB-009: Soft delete sets Inactive
  - BR-SUB-011: Public API shows Published only
  - BR-SUB-012: Non-admin cannot see Inactive
end note

@enduml
